In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney stated that there is no deal on the debt ceiling and that no progress has been made. He emphasized that the President is committed to getting the biggest deficit reduction package possible, and that it must be balanced and address all drivers of long-term debt. Carney also clarified that the President is opposed to a short-term extension of the debt ceiling and that he wants a deal that takes the country through 2013. He mentioned that discussions are ongoing and that the President remains optimistic that a significant deficit reduction can be achieved. Carney also addressed questions about the space shuttle program ending and the situation in Syria.